          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Tritium-loaded titanium foil, with width of 4.5 mm",
                "and thickness of 0.5 mg/cm**2. The tritium /",
                "titanium ratio was 1.3:1, corresponding to an",
                "effective tritium thickness of 36 ug/cm**2."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The radioactive 44Ar beam was produced by 1.4-GeV",
                "protons on an uranium carbide target. The target was",
                "heated to reduce contamination via CO2. The 44Ar ions",
                "then were transferred into the FEBIAD ion source to",
                "achieve high ionization efficiency for 1+ state.",
                "Afterwards, the ions were accelerated to 30 keV and",
                "led through the HRS separator. The ions were then",
                "accumulated in the REX trap for 60 ms, before",
                "injection into the REX EBIS ion source. Before",
                "acceleration the ions were separated by their mass to",
                "charge ratio."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SISD"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " T-REX silicon detector array"
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "HPGE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " MINIBALL germanium detector array"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "EDE",
                "EXTB",
                "GSPEC",
                "SITA"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                "The 44Ar(t,p) transfer reaction",
                "was studied by radioactive beams at REX ISOLDE, The",
                "44Ar ions were accelerated by the REX LINAC to 2.16",
                "MeV, and directed to the tritiated titanium target.",
                "The average beam intensity was 2*10**5 ions/sec. The",
                "angular distribution of protons from the reaction was",
                "measured. Doppler corrected gamma spectra were also",
                "acquired."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ADD-RES": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "COMP"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The experimental results were compared with",
                "theoretical calculations using the DWBA reaction model."
              ]
            }
          ],
